name: SVGRect
description: The SVGRect represents a rectangle. Rectangles consist of an x and y coordinate pair identifying a minimum x value, a minimum y value, and a width and height, which are constrained to be non-negative.

members.name: SVGRect.x
members.description: The exact effect of this coordinate depends on each element. If the attribute is not specified, the effect is as if a value of 0 were specified.

members.name: SVGRect.y
members.description: The exact effect of this coordinate depends on each element.If the attribute is not specified, the effect is as if a value of 0 were specified.

members.name: SVGRect.width
members.description: This represents the width of the rectangle.A value that is negative results to an error. A value of zero disables rendering of the element

members.name: SVGRect.height
members.description: This represents the height of the rectangle.A value that is negative results to an error.A value of zero disables rendering of the element.
